page.title: 01A DAY IN THE LIFE OF RACHEL
page.content: The alarm wakes me up at 8.00 o'clock. I get up and go to the bathroom but nearly always someone is in there. I go into the kitchen and eat my breakfast. I hate breakfast. I get dressed after lots of thought on what to wear and go to school. Usually we read but I'm still half asleep so I have difficulty. We do Maths for an hour but the bell rings so we go into the hall for service. At 11.00 am we come in after play. We have lunch at 12.o'clock; I'm very hungry so I eat mine in about five minutes.We go out for break until 1.15 pm. If it isn't games then we usually do art or science in the afternoon. When I get home I'm hungry and tired so I have a snack. At dinner I get teased by my brother and sister. Then I watch television. When I'm tired I go to bed.
